  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf  \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd ; \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb5\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The husband who abducted his wife seeking divorce; Three detained - incident in Batticaloa",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "A husband and parents have been arrested for abducting his wife seeking divorce in a tricycle at Jayanthipuram Praset in Batticaloa Headquarters Police Division.",
        "The Batticaloa Magistrate's Court ordered the three arrested persons to be remanded until next Monday on Friday (29).",
        "A woman who lived in Jayanthipuram Praset in Batticaloa Police Headquarters got married to a man from the same area 6 months ago.",
        "In this case, there is a conflict between husband and wife. Subsequently, the said woman has separated from her husband 3 months ago and is living with her parents, and has filed a case in court seeking divorce from her husband.",
        "On the day of the incident, Friday morning (29), 3 persons including the husband and her parents went on a tricycle and besieged the wife's house.",
        "In this case, the husband assaulted the wife's mother and her two sisters and kidnapped the wife and locked her in the room of his house.",
        "In addition, after complaining to the 119 Police Emergency Service that her sister had been abducted, the Divisional Headquarters Police rescued the woman who had been abducted and locked her in a room and arrested 3 people including the abducted woman's husband and her parents.",
        "When the 3 arrested persons were brought before the Batticaloa Magistrate's Court yesterday evening, the Magistrate ordered them to be arraigned on the coming Monday."
      ],
